@node WHY "OHAC:  No!  Not ANOTHER Calendar!  Please, No!!!"
@next NEEDS

  @{b}Why?@{ub}

  Once upon a time, our @{"local user group" link ACE} meeting needed to be rescheduled,
and an e-mail of possible alternate dates was circulated.  Recieving this
mail, I was faced with several options:

  @{"a" link DOOR#1})  Walk across the room & flip through a physical calendar.
  @{"b" link DOOR#2})  Open the Time preferences program.
  @{"c" link DOOR#3})  Download one of the 374 calendar programs already in existence.
  @{"d" link DOOR#4})  Reply with the usual, "Any of these days are fine with me."
      (One of the many benefits of having no life whatsoever).
  @{"e" link DOOR#5})  Create a calendar program of my very own.

  Option "e" was, of course, the obvious, most desirable course of action.


@{u}@{b}Features:@{ub}@{uu}
  o Font-sensitive, resizable, localized, GadTools GUI.
  o Select a date, and the number of days from/since today will be reported.
  o "Dates" menu with user-definable dates.
  o Calendar ranges from Jan. 1, 1978 to Dec. 31, 2113.
  o Can open on any public screen, and jump from screen to screen.
  o AmigaGuide docs that are more fun than a severe beating!
  o It's free!  And the source code (in Amiga E) is included.
@endnode

