@node ACE "OHAC:  Free Plug Dept."
@next ACE
@prev ACE

              @{i}Fascinating Facts About:@{ui}
@{b}ACE - Amiga Computer Enthusiasts of Elkhart, Indiana (USA)@{ub}

o ACE is Elkhart Indiana's largest, finest, (and only) Amiga users group!

o It meets at 11:30 am (usually) on the second Saturday of each month (seven
  times out of ten).

o Everyone is welcome to attend (Even Bill Gates?  Well... why not?  If he
  could be turned from the Dark Side he could become a powerful ally...)!

o No dues, cover-charges, or membership fees!
  (Plenty of synonyms, though...)

o Learn the secret handshake (so secret even we don't know it)!

o ACE is an official member of the Amiga User Group Network (UGN).

o Visit the official ACE Web pages (in color!) at:
  http://home.earthlink.net/~gregdonner/ace/ace.html
@endnode


@node NEEDS "OHAC:  Requirements"

@{u}@{b}Required:@{ub}@{uu}
  - An Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or above.
  - Workbench 2.1 or above is required for localization (locale.library v38).
  - calendar.gadget (included).
@endnode


@node STUFFIT "OHAC:  Installation"

@{u}@{b}Installation:@{ub}@{uu}
  - Copy the calendar.gadget (OHAC/classes/gadgets) to somewhere in your LIBS:
   path.  "SYS:Classes/Gadgets/" is the usual location.
    The supplied calendar.gadget is v42.1.

  - OHAC itself may be placed anywhere (within reason).
@endnode


@node STARTMEUP "OHAC:  If You Start Me Up..."
@next GUI

@{u}@{b}Startup Options:@{ub}@{uu}
  OHAC accepts the following keywords as tooltypes or CLI arguments.
All are optional.

@{u}Keyword        @{uu}  @{u}CLI Shortcut@{uu}  @{u}Argument     @{uu}  @{u}Default Setting              @{uu}
@{"LEFTEDGE      " link OPT_POS}  X             -1 - 65535     -1 - Centered.
@{"TOPEDGE       " link OPT_POS}  Y             -1 - 65535     -1 - Centered.
@{"WIDTH         " link OPT_POS}  W             0 - 65535      0 (minimum width).
@{"HEIGHT        " link OPT_POS}  H             0 - 65535      0 (minimum height).
@{"PUBSCREEN     " link OPT_PS}  PS            Screen name.   Default public screen.
@{"FONT          " link OPT_FONT}  F             Font name.     Default screen font.
@{"FONTSIZE      " link OPT_FONT}  FS            Point size.    Default screen font size.
@{"ICONIFY       " link OPT_HIDE}  I             None.          OHAC's window opens when run.
@{"ICONIFIEDIMAGE" link OPT_HIDE}  IMG           Icon name.     Use OHAC's icon.
@{"SETTODAY      " link OPT_DATE}  SD            dd.mm.yyyy     Current date.
@{"SHOWDATE      " link OPT_DATE}  SD            dd.mm.yyyy     Current date.
@{"DATEMENU      " link OPT_DATE}  DM            dd.mm.yyyy     None.
@endnode

@node OPT_POS "OHAC:  Window Position & Dimension Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Window Position Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}X@{ub}, @{b}LEFTEDGE@{ub} <-1 - 65535>
@{b}Y@{ub}, @{b}TOPEDGE@{ub}  <-1 - 65535>

  These two keywords set the initial position OHAC's window will open at.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  -1 - Centered.

---

@{u}@{b}Window Dimension Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}W@{ub}, @{b}WIDTH@{ub}  <0 - 65535>
@{b}H@{ub}, @{b}HEIGHT@{ub} <0 - 65535>

  These two keywords set the dimensions OHAC's window will initially open to.
OHAC may adjust these values to fit the screen size and the minimum space
required to create the GUI.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  0 (Smallest possible width/height).
@endnode

@node OPT_PS "OHAC:  Public Screen Keyword"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Public Screen Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}PS@{ub}, @{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub} <screen name>

  The public screen OHAC should open on.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  Default public screen.
@endnode

@node OPT_FONT "OHAC:  Font Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Font Keywords:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}F@{ub}, @{b}FONT@{ub} <font name>

  Font to use in OHAC's window.  It isn't necessary to supply the ".font"
extension.


@{b}FS@{ub}, @{b}FONTSIZE@{ub} <point size>

  What size the font specified by @{b}FONT@{ub} should be.


@{b}Notes:@{ub}
  o  In order to use a custom font, both @{b}FONT@{ub} and @{b}FONTSIZE@{ub} must be specified.

  o  The font may be changed after startup with the @{"Change Font" link MENU_FONT} menu item.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  Default screen font.
@endnode

@node OPT_HIDE "OHAC:  Iconify Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Iconify Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}I@{ub}, @{b}ICONIFY@{ub}

  This keyword tells OHAC not to open its window when run; rather an icon
will appear on the Workbench screen.  Double-clicking this icon will open
OHAC's window.


@{b}Note:@{ub}  OHAC may be iconified at any time using the @{"Iconify" link MENU_HIDE} menu item.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  OHAC is not iconified at startup.

---

@{b}IMG@{ub}, @{b}ICONIFIEDIMAGE@{ub} <icon name>

  When OHAC is iconified, it will use the image of the icon specified by this
keyword.  It isn't necessary to supply the ".info" extension.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  OHAC's icon's image is used, or the default Tool image if no icon
         exists for OHAC.
@endnode

@node OPT_DATE "OHAC:  Date Keywords"
@toc STARTMEUP
@next STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}Set Today Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}ST@{ub}, @{b}SETTODAY@{ub} <dd.mm.yyyy>

  OHAC will use this date as the current date, i.e. "today".
All days-since/days-until reports will be measured from this date.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  The current date.

---

@{u}@{b}Show Date Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}SD@{ub}, @{b}SHOWDATE@{ub} <dd.mm.yyyy text>

  OHAC will display this date when first run.
  It will also become the second item in the @{"Dates" link MENU_DATES} menu.


@{b}Default:@{ub}  The current date.

---

@{u}@{b}Date Menu Keyword:@{ub}@{uu}
@{b}DM@{ub}, @{b}DATEMENU@{ub} <dd.mm.yyyy text>

  This keyword adds dates to the @{"Dates" link MENU_DATES} menu.


@{b}DATEMENU Usage from the CLI:@{ub}
  When running OHAC from the CLI give one "DATEMENU" keyword and then the
dates after it.  Use quotation marks if any dates contain spaces.
@{i}Example:  @{ui}DATEMENU "25.12.???? - Christmas" 01.01.2000 13.12.????

@{b}DATEMENU Usage as a Tooltype:@{ub}
  Supply one date after each "DATEMENU", and use multiple "DATEMENU" keywords.
Quotation marks are not necessary.
@{i}Example:  @{ui}DATEMENU=25.12.???? - Christmas
          DATEMENU=01.01.2000
          DATEMENU=13.12.????

---

@{u}@{b}Date Format:@{ub}@{uu}
OHAC expects dates to be entered as:  dd.mm.yyyy
  A two digit day (00 - 31),
  a seperator character (any character except "$", "%", """, or a number),
  a two digit month (01 - 12),
  a seperator character,
  a four digit year (1978 - 2113).

  Extra text is ignorred, but will appear in the @{"Dates" link DATES} menu.

  If non-numeric characters are enterd in place of a day, month, or year
  OHAC will use the current day, month, or year.

@{i}Examples:@{ui}
@{u}Date:                 @{uu}       @{u}OHAC will display:                            @{uu}
25.12.xxxx - Christmas       Dec. 25 of the current year.
01.01.2000                   Jan. 1, 2000.
??/??/1978                   The current month and day in the year 1978.
xx-xx-xxxx                   The current date.
25/9/1990                    Not what you want; the month must be 2 digits.
25 09 1990                   Sept. 25, 1990.
@endnode


@node GUI "OHAC:  The GUI"
@next MENUS
@prev STARTMEUP

@{u}@{b}OHAC's Main (and only) Window:@{ub}@{uu}
  OHAC's GUI bears more than a passing resemblence to the following:

                @{bg fill}|o| OHAC v1.3                 |' |[]|@{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background} __________________  _____  _  _ @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}|@|   April        ||1999 ||<||>|@{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background} ------------------  -----  -  - @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}Sun  Mon  Tue  Wed  Thu  Fri  Sat@{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}                    1    2    3  @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}4    5    6    7    8    9    10 @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}11   12   13   14   15   16   17 @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}18   19   20   21   22   23   24 @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}25   26   27   28  @{bg fill} 29 @{bg background}  30      @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}                                 @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background} ________________________  _____ @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background}|43 days ago.            ||Today|@{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}  @{bg background} ------------------------  ----- @{bg fill}  @{bg background}
                @{bg fill}                                   /|@{bg background}

  The year gadget (upper right) accepts years from 1978 to 2113, and the
buttons beside it decrement/increment the year by 1 (click), 5 (Shift-click),
or 10 (Alt-click).

  The text display gadget in the bottom left reports the number of days
away from today, or the word "Today."

  The "Today" button (bottom right) resets the month, year, and calendar
gadgets to today's (hence the name) date.
  SHIFT-Today (clicking on the "Today" button while either Shift key is
depressed) will convince OHAC that "today" is the currently displayed date.
Thus all days-since/days-until reports will be measured from this date.
  ALT-Today will reset OHAC to the current system date.
@endnode


